main event: NAVY aircrews reported observing several glowing objects falling through the air toward the sea.
interesting points: The sighting involved glowing objects passing through cloud layers at approximately 18,000 feet., The observation time was recorded as 23/0842Z on 7 November 1962., The location of the sighting was at latitude 20°21'N and longitude 174°30'W in the Pacific., There were multiple observations from military aircraft., The objects were categorized as possibly being ballistic, balloons, aircraft, or astronomical, but evaluation was insufficient.
